P(k,s)=\frac{1}{2(1-\phi_1(k,s)\phi_2(k,s))}\left[\frac{\phi_1(k,s)\phi_2(k,s)}{\lambda}+\frac{\phi_1(k,s)\phi_2(k,s)}{\gamma}+\frac{\phi_2(k,s)}{\gamma}++\frac{\phi_1(k,s)}{\lambda}\right] 
\phi_\alpha(k,s)=p_\alpha(R|t)\phi_\alpha(t),\\ p_\alpha(R|t)=\frac{1}{4\pi D_\alpha t}\exp\left(-\frac{R^2}{4D_\alpha t}\right)\\\phi_\alpha(t)=\psi_\alpha\exp(-\psi_\alpha t)\\\alpha=1,2\quad\psi_1=\lambda\quad \psi_2=\gamma
